rComments: Bianca is a solid teacher who is very friendly and caring. We had inverted class where you do worksheets and can ask her questions in real time. Her assignments were cut up in phases such that by the end you would have a cool C application you can use. She made PCRS worth 10% for us!!! Her midterm was bit tough, but final was easy with cheat-sheet.

Nicest prof I've ever had so far. To do well in this course going to class will help, but doing, and understanding the weekly PCRS/Labs perfectly is where the majority of your marks will come from. All the marks you will earn from assignments and exams will be directly correlated to the PCRS.
She's a very nice comp sci prof, and gives very fair exams.
Very good in explaining concepts but gives assignments that are a bit tricky.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']
